From: Hien Huynh <hien.huynh.px@renesas.com>
Date: Thu, 30 May 2019 14:52:14 +0700
Subject: [PATCH 074/350] sched: Wrap rq->rd->overload accesses with
 READ/WRITE_ONCE

This variable can be read and set locklessly within
update_sd_lb_stats().
As such, READ/WRITE_ONCE are added to make sure nothing terribly
wrong can happen because of the compiler.

Cherry-picked from https://patchwork.kernel.org/patch/10506529/

cc: Ingo Molnar <mingo@redhat.com>
cc: Peter Zijlstra <peterz@infradead.org>

Signed-off-by: Valentin Schneider <valentin.schneider@arm.com>
Signed-off-by: Morten Rasmussen <morten.rasmussen@arm.com>
Signed-off-by: Gaku Inami <gaku.inami.xh@renesas.com>
Signed-off-by: Hien Huynh <hien.huynh.px@renesas.com>
---
 kernel/sched/fair.c  | 6 +++---
 kernel/sched/sched.h | 4 ++--
 2 files changed, 5 insertions(+), 5 deletions(-)

diff --git a/kernel/sched/fair.c b/kernel/sched/fair.c
index 9ee043d..6af360e 100644
--- a/kernel/sched/fair.c
+++ b/kernel/sched/fair.c
@@ -8279,8 +8279,8 @@ static inline void update_sd_lb_stats(struct lb_env *env, struct sd_lb_stats *sd
 
 	if (!env->sd->parent) {
 		/* update overload indicator if we are at root domain */
-		if (env->dst_rq->rd->overload != overload)
-			env->dst_rq->rd->overload = overload;
+		if (READ_ONCE(env->dst_rq->rd->overload) != overload)
+			WRITE_ONCE(env->dst_rq->rd->overload, overload);
 	}
 }
 
@@ -9737,7 +9737,7 @@ static int idle_balance(struct rq *this_rq, struct rq_flags *rf)
 	rq_unpin_lock(this_rq, rf);
 
 	if (this_rq->avg_idle < sysctl_sched_migration_cost ||
-	    !this_rq->rd->overload) {
+			!READ_ONCE(this_rq->rd->overload)) {
 
 		rcu_read_lock();
 		sd = rcu_dereference_check_sched_domain(this_rq->sd);
diff --git a/kernel/sched/sched.h b/kernel/sched/sched.h
index d2923ab..c389979 100644
--- a/kernel/sched/sched.h
+++ b/kernel/sched/sched.h
@@ -1699,8 +1699,8 @@ static inline void add_nr_running(struct rq *rq, unsigned count)
 
 	if (prev_nr < 2 && rq->nr_running >= 2) {
 #ifdef CONFIG_SMP
-		if (!rq->rd->overload)
-			rq->rd->overload = 1;
+		if (!READ_ONCE(rq->rd->overload))
+			WRITE_ONCE(rq->rd->overload, 1);
 #endif
 	}
 
